    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-salt-and-pepper-hake-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>hake</strong> <strong>fillets</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-salt-and-pepper-hake-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped hake</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cornflour </strong>and <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>gluten free soy sauce </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up so the hake is fully coated</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining cornflour</strong> to a separate bowl</p><p>Add the<strong> coated hake</strong> to the bowl with the remaining cornflour and give everything a good mix up until all the hake is coated</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-salt-and-pepper-hake-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onions</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-salt-and-pepper-hake-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>coated hake </strong>with a good grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min on each side until golden and crispy and cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once cooked through, add the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>sliced chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and your <strong>ginger and garlic paste</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy salt & pepper hake</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-salt-and-pepper-hake-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, remove the <strong>outer leaves</strong> and set aside, then shred the <strong>inner core</strong></p><p>Peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of <strong>carrot ribbons</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-salt-and-pepper-hake-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and <strong>chilli relish </strong>to a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and the <strong>remaining gluten free soy sauce </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>sweet chilli dressing</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>cooked rice</strong>, <strong>sliced cucumber</strong>, <strong>carrot ribbons </strong>and <strong>lettuce</strong> to a large bowl with the<strong> sweet chilli dressing</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> sweet chilli rice salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-salt-and-pepper-hake-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> crispy salt & pepper hake</strong> over the <strong>sweet chilli</strong> <strong>rice salad</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
